<HEADLINE>
LAKERS HOPE COMING HOME RECHARGES THEIR AILING GAME
</HEADLINE>
 LAKERS-LADN (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. _ How did the Los Angeles Lakers lose a
winnable game Wednesday? They would count the ways, but it might
take a couple of hours. And besides, they're probably worn out from
kicking themselves for 2,000 miles on the plane ride back home.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Kurt Rambis gave his team the day off Thursday _ all the
better to clear their heads of various mental debris left from
their Game 2 implosion to the San Antonio Spurs.
</P>
<P>
   ``It helps mentally to get away from it for a few hours,
regRo,\%' Z,-Ho
</P>
