   NY-SUBURBAN-SLUMS (Undated) _ Behind drawn curtains in nearly
every town and village on Long Island, tens of thousands of legal
and illegal immigrants from Central America and Mexico are jammed
into subdivided houses and partitioned apartments, biding their
time in invisible suburban slums that local officials say they have
little hope of controlling. By Charlie LeDuff and David M.
Halbfinger.
