   FEATURES/LIFESTYLE (``l'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   YADDO-AUTHORS (Albany, N.Y.) _ The 1940s at the Yaddo estate at
Saratoga Springs was its Southern period, led by the writers Carson
McCullers, Eudora Welty and Katherine Anne Porter. Other artists at
Yaddo at the time included Langston Hughes, Flannery O'Connor,
Robert Lowell, Granville Hicks, Henri Cartier-Bresson, Eleanor
Clark, Patricia Highsmith, Theodore Roethke, Alfred Kazin and
Marguerite Young. By KATE GURNETT. (For release Sunday, May 23.)
</P>
