another Englishman may offer sounder guidance. In ``Henry VI,''
William Shakespeare wrote: Thrice is he arm'd that hath his quarrel
just, And he but naked, though lock'd up in steel, Whose conscience
with injustice is corrupted. By ALEX A. VARDAMIS.
