<HEADLINE>
EDITORS:    
</HEADLINE>
  
 Friday, May 21, 1999
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service will file this additional story for
Saturday in the ``w'' category:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-INVASION (Washington) _ Although NATO has all but ruled
out a ground invasion of Kosovo, U.S. Army Gen. Wesley Clark,
NATO's top commander, tells senior Pentagon officials that planning
is under way for a possible invasion. Pentagon spokesman Kenneth
Bacon says Clark told military leaders that ``you have to be open
to the possibility of looking at other options'' in addition to the
air campaign. By ERIC ROSENBERG.
</P>
<P>
   The Hearst News Service/Washington
</P>
</TEXT>
