A6277 &Cx1f; ttg-z
a k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-GRIMES-HUMOR-COLUMN-$     05-21 0520
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GRIMES-HUMOR-COLUMN-$ADV24-NYTR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
COLUMN: BETTER LEFT UNSAID 
</HEADLINE>
   (For release Monday May 24)  
 By DAVID GRIMES   
 Sarasota (Fla.) Herald-Tribune   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Things you'd rather not hear...
</P>
<P>
   During surgery
</P>
<P>
   1. Everybody stand back! I lost my contact lens!
</P>
<P>
   2. Rex! Come back with that! Bad dog!
</P>
<P>
   3. Could you stop that thing from thumping? It's throwing my
concentration off!
</P>
<P>
   4. Wait a minute! If that's his kidney, then what's this?
</P>
<P>
   5. What do you mean he wasn't in for a sex change?
</P>
<P>
   During a tax audit
</P>
<P>
   1. Is this meant to be some sort of joke?
</P>
<P>
   2. If you sold your house today, what do you think you could get
for it?
</P>
<P>
   3. Don't think of it as prison; think of it as free room and
board.
</P>
<P>
   4. I hope you haven't made any plans for the next 20 years.
</P>
<P>
   5. You were close; you were only off by five decimal points.
</P>
<P>
   During a job performance review
</P>
<P>
   1. You weren't planning on making this your career, were you?
</P>
<P>
   2. On the positive side, you keep a very neat desk.
</P>
<P>
   3. You say your name is Grimes? I thought we fired you three
years ago.
</P>
<P>
   4. It's not that we're unhappy with your performance. We just
think you'd be happier if your desk were moved out to the parking
lot.
</P>
<P>
   5. Look on the positive side: You won't have to bring a covered
dish to the company picnic this summer.
</P>
<P>
   From your kid
</P>
<P>
   1. Binoculars aren't expensive, are they?
</P>
<P>
   2. Before you go in the house, you might want to take off your
shoes.
</P>
<P>
   3. Your credit card? I thought it was our credit card!
</P>
<P>
   4. Honest, I was just trying to dry Fluffy off in the microwave.
How was I to know she'd explode?
</P>
<P>
   5. Grades are so arbitrary, don't you think?
</P>
<P>
   From your auto mechanic
</P>
<P>
   1. Who'd you buy this from?
</P>
<P>
   2. I've got some good news and some bad news. The good news is
we take credit cards ...
</P>
<P>
   3. When was the last time you had an engine overhaul?
</P>
<P>
   4. Can you show me how to open your hood?
</P>
<P>
   5. I can never remember: Is it clockwise tighten or
counterclockwise tighten?
</P>
<P>
   On a blind date
</P>
<P>
   1. Look at this and tell me if you think it's infected.
</P>
<P>
   2. Mind if my mother tags along?
</P>
<P>
   3. Phew! I shouldn't have had that second bowl of chili for
lunch.
</P>
<P>
   4. It probably won't happen, but if I do have a seizure, just
stick your belt in my mouth.
</P>
<P>
   5. I refuse to shave my legs for any man.
</P>
<P>
   From your waiter
</P>
<P>
   1. I don't know. Smells OK to me.
</P>
<P>
   2. If you ask for more rolls one more time I'll slit your
throat!
</P>
<P>
   3. Chicken, fish. What's the difference.
</P>
<P>
   4. Would you mind wiping my nose? I've got my hands full.
</P>
<P>
   5. Anybody want to buy some crack?
</P>
<P>
   From your psychiatrist
</P>
<P>
   1. Don't tell me your troubles, pal! I got problems of my own!
</P>
<P>
   2. You want a second opinion? OK, you're ugly, too!
</P>
<P>
   3. Could you talk a little faster? I've got a tee time at 11:30.
</P>
<P>
   4. If I were you I'd shoot myself.
</P>
<P>
   5. When I was in school, we used to beat up kids like you.
</P>
<P>
   (The Herald-Tribune in Sarasota, Fla., is part of the New York
Times Regional Newspaper Group.)
</P>
</TEXT>
