<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    IN ALBANIA, INTERNET PROVIDES NATIVES, REFUGEES WINDOW TO
OUTSIDE WORLD
 &HT;    With Photo.
 &HT;    Moving in both (i) International and (f) financial categories.
 &HT;    By BERT ROUGHTON JR. 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   TIRANA, Albania _ In a small room one floor up from a narrow,
muddy street here in Albania's capital, you can rent a window on
the world for $3 an hour.
</P>
<P>
   For Leohora Lutolli, a 21-year-old refugee from Kosovo, the
