<SLUG> BC-SHOOT-BARR22-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Barr: Don't blame guns for plague of violence
 &HT;    By Rebecca Carr
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ U.S. Rep. Bob Barr says he plans to do whatever it
takes to stop guns from becoming ``the scapegoat'' on Capitol Hill
for teen violence.
</P>
<P>
   As the Georgia Republican sees it, guns are unfairly being
blamed for the wounding of six students Thursday at Heritage High
School near Conyers, Ga., and a shooting rampage that killed 15
people at a Colorado high school last month.
</P>
<P>
   ``The media will blame guns, not culture, parental
responsibility or school responsibility,'' said Barr, a board
member of the National Rifle Association.
</P>
<P>
   As for the 15-year-old student who opened fire on his fellow
students at Heritage: ``I'm not interested in giving this kid bear
hugs _ they ought to put him in shackles,'' Barr said.
</P>
<P>
   Juvenile shooters should be tried as adults, he added.
</P>
<P>
   ``I hope people are seriously asking themselves why this kid did
this,'' Barr said. ``I hope they realize that our culture is
responsible for this act, not our guns.''
</P>
<P>
   Barr is gearing up for an all-out battle next week when a
subcommittee of the House Judiciary Committee holds a second
hearing on the causes of teen violence.
</P>
<P>
   Barr was distressed by the gun control measure approved in the
Senate on Thursday, saying it did not address the larger question
of why young people are becoming more violent today.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think some Republicans are operating more scared than
responsibly,'' said Barr, referring to the six Senate Republicans
who voted with Democrats to require background checks on all people
who buy firearms at gun shows.
</P>
<P>
   ``What happened in Conyers ... would not be impacted by any of
the proposed laws or the ones that already exist,'' Barr said. ``We
have more gun control than we had 20 years ago, yet we have more
violence. Clearly the answer is not more laws.''
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
