   BC-MET-APPOINT-NYT (moved on Thursday, May 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Thursday, May 20,
about the election of Paul M. Montrone as president and chief
executive of the Metropolitan Opera Association referred
imprecisely to the association's role in hiring. The association is
responsible for hiring the Met's general manager. It is the general
manager, not the association, who hires the artistic director.
