   &UR; ON THE SECTION FRONT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   RENAULT-NISSAN (Undated) _ The lessons for Renault, as it takes
control of Nissan, in Ford's experience at Mazda. By Stephanie
Strom and Keith Bradsher. &UR;  &LR; (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic and Photo.
</P>
<P>
   CREDITCARDS-COMPETITION (Undated) _ American Express faces
serious competition for the charge card business of the rich, whose
numbers are growing along with the stock market, from a variety of
financial services businesses. By David Cay Johnston. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   MARKET-WATCH (New York) _ A weekly feature looking at
developments of the market worldwide. By Gretchen Morgenson.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INSIDE THE SECTION &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-PROFILE-TRUJILLO (subsked) (Undated) _ Profile of Solomon D.
Trujillo, chairman and chief executive of US West Inc. By Seth
Schiesel. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-BRIEFS (Undated) _ A weekly column of short items on people
and personalities that make business more than a dollars and cents
proposition. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-ECON-COLUMN (Undated) _ The Economic View column. Now that
inflation may be creeping back into the economy, it's worth noting
that it might not be such a bad thing, and looking at who benefits.
By Louis Uchitelle. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-5-QUESTIONS (Undated) _ Five questions for Jeffrey C. Smith,
head of the trade association that represents pollution control
equipment makers, on the court ruling tossing out new EPA smog
rules. By Claudia H. Deutsch. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo.
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-TRACTORS (Undated) _ What customers really want to know
about the merger between Case and New Holland is, what color will
the tractors be? This isn't as silly a question as it seems: In the
farm equipment business, where brand loyalty is high, customers are
very attached to their favorite brand's signature color, and you
can tell who made a tractor from miles away. By Andrew Bluth.
(Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-PENNIES (Undated) _ The great penny shortage in eastern
Missouri is over. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-DIARY (Undated) _ Short items on surveys, research and new
consumer products. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   BIZ-ANIMATION-FILMS (Studio City, Calif.) _ Who needs the
studios? A golden age is blossoming for entrepeneurs in the film
business, especially the animation houses and special effects shops
that have figured out they can make whole movies themselves. By
Joel Kotkin. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Photo
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-ASSISTED-LIVING (Undated) _ Assisted Living Co. stocks
are the walking dead, down 30 percent this year. The culprit: a
negative analyst report from February whose author admits she was
wrong. The lesson: tread carefully in the land of illiquid
small-caps. By David J. Morrow. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic and Photo.
</P>
<P>
   INVEST-EMERGING-MARKETS (Undated) _ Three financial strategists
and others reviewed their outlook last week to accommodate the fact
that the Federal Reserve is now leaning toward raising its
short-term interest rate. By Jonathan Fuerbringer. (Moved).
</P>
<P>
   With Graphic.
</P>
