<SLUG> BC-BOX-OSCARSIDE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
NEXT UP: DE LA HOYA-TRINIDAD
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By MICHAEL ROSENTHAL  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LAS VEGAS _ Oscar De La Hoya finally has his big fight.
</P>
<P>
   He will face Felix Trinidad in a title unification bout and the
biggest non-heavyweight matchup possible Sept. 18 at the Mandalay
Bay Events Center, it was announced Friday.
</P>
<P>
   De La Hoya, the WBC welterweight champion, will earn at least a
career-high $15 million; Trinidad, the IBF champ, at least $11
million.
</P>
<P>
   ``What other alternative does (Trinidad) have?'' said Bob Arum,
De La Hoya's promoter. ``Who else can he fight and make this kind
of money?
</P>
<P>
   ``If he wins, he's on top of the world. If he loses, he'll
probably not be marketable for (promoter) Don King anymore.''
</P>
<P>
   It was unclear whether the fight would materialize until the
Friday deadline promoter Bob Arum had set.
</P>
<P>
   Felix Trinidad Sr., the fighter's father, would not accept
Arum's offer of $10 million plus $6 for every pay-per-view buy over
1 million.
</P>
<P>
   This week, Arum, with help from Time-Warner, HBO's parent
company, raised the ante to $11 million and lowered the number of
buys to 850,000.
</P>
<P>
   That was good enough for Trinidad's camp, which agreed to the
deal Friday.
</P>
<P>
   Apparently, De La Hoya's take also will rise. Arum now says his
fighter is guaranteed $15 million and could make as much as $20
million if the fight does well on television.
</P>
<P>
   ``It took a while for (Trinidad's people) to realize that Oscar
was going to make the lion's share of the money,'' Arum said.
</P>
<P>
   The bout, like De La Hoya-Ike Quartey matchup in February, is a
throwback to the days of Sugar Ray Leonard, Tommy Hearns, Marvin
Hagler and Roberto Duran. And it's one that De La Hoya, eager to
enhance his legacy, desperately wanted.
</P>
<P>
   De La Hoya and Trinidad are a combined 64-0, with 53 knockouts.
De La Hoya is 30-0, 24 KOs. Trinidad is 34-0, 29 KOs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-05-21-99 2229EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
