<HEADLINE>
HOME RUN IN 11TH LIFTS ST. JOHN'S OVER WEST VIRGINIA IN BIG EAST
TOURNAMENT
</HEADLINE>
   (rk) 
 By STEVE POPPER   
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service    
<TEXT>
<P>
   Mike Dzurilla's teammates describe him as a pure hitter, and
like most pure hitters he was not interested in cluttering his mind
with details when he stepped to the plate with two runners on base
in the bottom of the 11th inning Friday in Trenton.
</P>
<P>
   If he had, he might have known that Billy Biggs, the West
Virginia reliever, had not surrendered a home run all season and
that the freshman pitcher's best pitch was a slider. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   With St. John's tied with West Virginia, 6-6, and facing
elimination from the Big East Conference tournament and the end of
its season, Dzurilla just looked for a pitch that he could handle.
He drilled the first pitch, a hanging slider, over the left-field
wall at Waterfront Park to lift St. John's to a 9-6 victory. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The home run erased the third baseman's frustration over
mishandling a bunt in the eighth inning, which had allowed West
Virginia to tie the score.
</P>
<P>
   The Red Storm will face Seton Hall Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   Dzurilla, a junior, tied the school record for home runs in a
season with his 15th, and he added to his own school record for
hits with three Friday, giving him 89 for the season.
</P>
<P>
   ``He came up big,'' St. John's coach Ed Blankmeyer said. ``You
want your best hitter up in a situation where you can win a ball
game.'' &QL;
</P>
<P>
   In the second game, Seton Hall stayed alive by handing
top-seeded Notre Dame its first loss of the tournament, 11-3. Alec
Porzel, Notre Dame's shortstop, hit his third home run to tie the
tournament home run record set by Scott DeMarrais of St. John's in
1986 and matched by Mo Vaughn of Seton Hall in 1989.
</P>
<P>
   Damon Ponce De Leon picked up the win and John Bravette had
three hits and two runs batted in for Seton Hall.
</P>
<P>
   Rutgers and Providence met in the final game of the day.  &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
